    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>You’ve created a custom toolkit for yourself called a holographic emitter. This functions as the @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.uWZ3LvxQ3yezLB4j]{custom rig} 1st-level mechanic ability but must either be a handheld device or worn. If you already have a custom rig, you instead gain a charlatan’s wand for free. You can use your holographic emitter to replicate rudimentary spell effects that involve light, allowing you to cast @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.spells.Item.rSWg5JnN3mxzkatD]{dancing lights}, @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.spells.Item.Lmo0TcZwLJs8yLfg]{glowing wall}, and @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.spells.Item.zWqiIrFHwfECEi20]{holographic interface} at will, though these effects are technological rather than magical in nature. Once per day, you can also cast @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.spells.Item.dIlKtUGGKcur6OaK]{wisp ally} as a technological effect. This increases to twice a day at 6th level and three times a day at 9th level.</p>"
    },
